        {
            "title": "Banana Nut Bread",
            "categories": ["Breads"],
            "author": "Merlin Salter",
            "content": [
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "Cream together:"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "name": "butter"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "cup", "name": "sugar"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "Add and beat in:"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "count", "name": "eggs"},
                        {"amount": 4, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "sour milk"},
                        {"amount": 3, "unit": "count", "name": "ripe bananas, mashed"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "Add and stir in:"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "cup", "name": "flour"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "tsp", "name": "baking soda"},
                        {"amount": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "name": "chopped pecans"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "Turn the batter into a buttered glass loaf pan and bake in a 350 degree for 1 hour or until a",
                        "toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.  Cool the bread in the pan for 10 to 15 minutes,",
                        "then loosen the edges with a knife blade and turn out onto a cutting board and continue to cool or",
                        "slice and serve.",
                        "",
                        "I sometimes double the recipe and freeze the second loaf.",
                        "",
                        "To make **sour milk**, combine the following with the milk (I’m convinced that this step is what",
                        "makes this banana bread so great. Use vinegar, not lemon juice.)"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "tsp", "name": "white vinegar"}
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Big Sandwich",
            "categories": ["Main Dishes"],
            "content": [
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "The big sandwich is a family favorite for casual dinners. The kids often requested it when we",
                        "were going out for the evening.",
                        "",
                        "## Ingredients"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "count", "name": "loaf freshly baked French bread"},
                        {"amount": 0.5, "unit": "count", "name": "head shredded iceberg lettuce"},
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "count", "name": "large tomatoes, sliced thinly"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "count", "name": "medium red onion, sliced thinly"},
                        {"amount": 0.75, "unit": "lb", "name": "thinly sliced deli ham"},
                        {"amount": 0.75, "unit": "lb", "name": "thinly sliced deli turkey"},
                        {"amount": 0.5, "unit": "lb", "name": "thinly sliced Swiss or Havarti cheese"},
                        {"amount": 0.125, "unit": "cup", "name": "mayonnaise"},
                        {"amount": 0.125, "unit": "cup", "name": "Dijon mustard"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "## Instructions",
                        "",
                        "1. Slice the French loaf in half lengthwise, if the loaf is really thick, scoop out some of the bread middle.",
                        "",
                        "2. Spread both sides liberally with mayo and as much mustard as you like.",
                        "",
                        "3. Layer the ham, turkey, and cheese on the bottom half of the loaf.",
                        "",
                        "4. Top with the tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste, onions and shredded lettuce.",
                        "",
                        "5. Place the top of the loaf on and wrap the whole sandwich tightly in saran wrap. Refrigerate until ready to slice."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Caesar Salad",
            "categories": ["Salads"],
            "content": [
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "## Dressing Ingredients"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "count", "name": "garlic cloves chopped"},
                        {"amount": 0.75, "unit": "tsp", "name": "salt"},
                        {"amount": 0.5, "unit": "tsp", "name": "Dijon mustard"},
                        {"amount": 1.5, "unit": "tsp", "name": "Worcestershire sauce"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "count", "name": "coddled egg"},
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "fresh lemon juice"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "tsp", "name": "anchovy paste"},
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "shredded Parmesan cheese"},
                        {"amount": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "name": "olive oil"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "## Salad Ingredients"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "count", "name": "large head romaine lettuce"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "cup", "name": "croutons"},
                        {"amount": 0.33, "unit": "cup", "name": "shredded Parmesan cheese"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "freshly ground black pepper"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "## Instructions",
                        "",
                        "1. In a blender, combine all of the dressing ingredients (except the olive oil) and process",
                        "   until smooth and thickened. Slowly blend in the olive oil.",
                        "",
                        "2. In a salad bowl, toss dressing with the salad ingredients.",
                        "",
                        "Dressing can be refrigerated up to 3 days.",
                        "",
                        "### How to Coddle an Egg",
                        "",
                        "To coddle an egg, bring 2 inches of water to boil in a small saucepan. Lower the egg (cracked open)",
                        "into the water, cover and let stand for 1 minute. Cool prior to adding to the blender."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Chunky Chippers",
            "categories": ["Cookies"],
            "content": [
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "## Ingredients"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "name": "butter"},
                        {"amount": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "name": "chunky peanut butter"},
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "count", "name": "eggs"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "cup", "name": "sugar"},
                        {"amount": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "name": "packed brown sugar"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "tsp", "name": "vanilla"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "water"},
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "cup", "name": "flour"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "tsp", "name": "baking soda"},
                        {"amount": 0.5, "unit": "tsp", "name": "salt"},
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "cup", "name": "chocolate chips"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "## Instructions",
                        "",
                        "1. Cream-together the butter, peanut butter, eggs, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla, and water.",
                        "",
                        "2. Stir-in the flour, baking soda, and salt.",
                        "",
                        "3. Stir-in the chocolate chips.",
                        "",
                        "Drop dough by large teaspoons onto a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for",
                        "12 to 14 minutes (cookies should be light brown and slightly underdone). Remove from sheet to cool."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Crescent Rolls",
            "categories": ["Breads"],
            "content": [
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "Stir together and dissolve:"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 0.75, "unit": "cup", "name": "warm water (110 degrees)"},
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "active dry yeast (two pkgs)"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "tsp", "name": "sugar"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "Let yeast mixture sit for about ten minutes.  Then add and stir in:"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "name": "butter, softened"},
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "count", "name": "eggs, beaten"},
                        {"amount": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "name": "sugar"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "tsp", "name": "salt"},
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "cup", "name": "flour"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "Then add and stir in:"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "cup", "name": "flour (additional)"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "Scrape down the sides of the bowl, cover with saran wrap, and let rise until double in a warm",
                        "place (about 1 1/2 hours).",
                        "",
                        "To form the dough for baking, punch down, and divide dough in half. On a floured surface, roll",
                        "each ball of dough into a 12” circle and spread with soft butter. Cut each circle into 12 wedges (like pizza).",
                        "Roll each wedge from the outer edge towards the tip and place tip side down on a lightly greased baking sheet,",
                        "leaving room for the rolls to expand. Cover the pans with a towel and place in a warm place to rise until double,",
                        "about an hour. Bake rolls in 400 degree oven for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown. Serve warm with butter."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Dilly Bread",
            "categories": ["Breads"],
            "author": "Helen Minkiewitz (Nonny)",
            "content": [
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "Soften and mix together and let stand for 10 minutes:"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "dry yeast"},
                        {"amount": 0.25, "unit": "cup", "name": "lukewarm water"},
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "sugar"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "Add and stir in:"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "cup", "name": "small curd cottage cheese, warmed"},
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "yellow onion, minced"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "butter, softened"},
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "tsp", "name": "dill seed"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "tsp", "name": "salt"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "count", "name": "egg, beaten"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "Mix in to form a sticky dough:"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 2.25, "unit": "cup", "name": "flour"},
                        {"amount": 0.25, "unit": "tsp", "name": "baking soda"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "Turn dough in a greased bowl and allow to rise until double in volume. Stir dough down, place",
                        "in a greased loaf pan and allow to rise until double again.",
                        "",
                        "Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes until loaf sounds hollow when thumped. Remove from the oven,",
                        "brush with butter and sprinkle with kosher salt. Cool in the pan for 15 minutes, then run a knife",
                        "blade around the edge, and remove from the loaf pan. Cut the loaf in thick slices and serve hot with",
                        "butter and lentil soup."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Gorgonzola Popovers",
            "categories": ["Appetizers"],
            "servings": {
                "count": 24,
                "size": {"amount": 1, "unit": "count", "name": "mini popover"}
            },
            "content": [
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "## Ingredients"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "count", "name": "large eggs"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "cup", "name": "room temperature milk"},
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "melted butter"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "cup", "name": "flour"},
                        {"amount": 0.5, "unit": "tsp", "name": "salt"},
                        {"amount": 0.125, "unit": "tsp", "name": "ground black pepper"},
                        {"amount": 1.25, "unit": "oz", "name": "Gorgonzola cheese"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "chopped fresh thyme"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "## Instructions",
                        "",
                        "1. Whisk together eggs, milk, melted butter, flour, salt, pepper, and thyme and refrigerate for 2 hours.",
                        "",
                        "2. Stir-in Gorgonzola cheese and thyme",
                        "",
                        "3. Butter 2 mini muffin pans. Fill each cup to the top with batter.",
                        "",
                        "Adjust the oven rack to the highest position in oven and bake at 425 degrees for 18 to 20 minutes",
                        "until puffed and golden.",
                        "",
                        "Great served as an appetizer with red wine."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Lentil Soup",
            "categories": ["Soups"],
            "content": [
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "Cook the following together in a 6 qt covered soup pot for 2 1/2 hours:"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 3, "unit": "cup", "name": "raw lentils"},
                        {"amount": 8, "unit": "cup", "name": "beef stock"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "tsp", "name": "salt"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "As you cook more liquid will be needed. Add water and return to a boil each time."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 8, "unit": "count", "name": "thick-cut bacon slices, diced"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "bacon drippings (from cooking the bacon)"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "Saute the bacon in a large skillet until crisp. Drain and set aside. Be sure to reserve",
                        "some of the bacon drippings.",
                        "",
                        "With the reserved bacon drippings in the skillet, saute the the following until",
                        "softened (about 7 to 10 minutes)."
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "minced garlic"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "count", "name": "large yellow onion, diced"},
                        {"amount": 3, "unit": "count", "name": "celery ribs, diced"},
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "count", "name": "large carrots, diced"},
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "count", "name": "large shallots, minced"},
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "count", "name": "fresh thyme sprigs"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "count", "name": "bay leaves"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "Add to the cooked lentils and simmer covered for 30 minutes more. Then add:"
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "ingredients": [
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "count", "name": "russet potato, peeled and diced"},
                        {"amount": 2, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "molasses"},
                        {"amount": 0.5, "unit": "cup", "name": "red wine"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "tbsp", "name": "worcestershire sauce"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "pinch", "name": "salt"},
                        {"amount": 1, "unit": "pinch", "name": "black pepper, freshly ground"}
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "markdown": [
                        "Cook covered for 30 minutes more. Add the crisped bacon and remove bay leaf and thyme sprigs.",
                        "",
                        "Store soup in a airtight container. Soup is better the second day. Freeze any leftover soup for another time.",
                        "",
                        "This was a favorite birthday dinner request with [Dilly Bread](#title=Dilly%20Bread)."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}
